<br>
On Friday I will post polls in the General Section where you can all vote for three new moderators.  The vote will remain open until Saturday, 11/15, at which time I will make the EZBoard changes necessary to place these three new (or returning) moderators in the Halls of Moderator Hell.  On 11/15 I will also step back into my position as Benevolent Administrator and will allow these new moderators to pick up any duties necessary.  THIS IS NOT A COUP, I DO NOT INTEND TO MODERATE THESE FORUMS INDEFINITELY!  <br>
<br>
Please do not send me any PMs telling me how unfair this is - I've been with these forums since their inception, and I intend to see that they continue in their glory for as long as I continue to play this game.  However it's time for someone to step up and get the new mods in place, and as admin that's mah (and Delaregar's, and Rinquist's) jobs.<br>
<br>
So, to summarize:<br>
<br>
1)  Polls go up Friday to vote in three mods.<br>
2)  Everyone has until 11/15 to vote.<br>
3)  Del, Rinquist and I will moderate until votes are done.<br>
4)  On 11/15 I will step back as moderator and just be admin.<br>
5)  The rule regarding in-game names in signatures is temporarily lifted until new mods are installed (then they can do as they wish with that rule).<br>
<br>
Oh, and by the way, Mausoleum requested that his userid be unbanned.  Like it or not, there's no real reason to deny his request, so he has been unbanned.  (He originally requested the ban, he was not banned due to behavior here or off of the forums.)<br>
<br>
That is all for now.<br>
<br>
Meridian <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;font-family:georgia;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Meridian Ascendant</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
